-- Bahrain's Al Baraka Bank posts 3.8 pct rise in Q2 net profit
-- By Nadia Saleem
-- Sun Aug 10, 2014 07:38AM EDT
-- None



DUBAI, Aug 10 (Reuters) - Al Baraka Banking Group <BARKA.BH>, a Bahrain-based Islamic lender with a presence in more than a dozen countries, posted a 3.8 percent increase in second-quarter net income, the bank said in a statement on Sunday.

The bank, which has operations in the Middle East, Asia and Africa, made a net attributable profit of $43.8 million for the three months to June 30, compared with $42.2 million in the year-ago period of 2013.